<HEAD>Poll Shows Dukakis 2-to-1 Over Bush in Iowa</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DES MOINES, Iowa (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Democrat Michael Dukakis holds a lead of
more than 2-to-1 over Republican George Bush among Iowans likely to
vote in the November presidential election, according to a new poll.
   The Massachusetts governor received support from 60 percent of
those surveyed compared to 28 percent for the vice president,
according to The Des Moines Register's Iowa Poll published Sunday.
   Another 11 percent said they are undecided and 1 percent said
they would support neither candidate.
   The poll was based on telephone responses from 670 randomly
selected Iowans who said they are likely to vote in November. The
survey, conducted June 7-14, had a margin of error of four
percentage points.
   Bush finished third behind Kansas Sen. Bob Dole and television
evangelist Pat Robertson in Iowa's early caucuses. Dukakis was
third behind Missouri Rep. Richard Gephardt and Illinois Sen. Paul
Simon.
</TEXT>
