<HEAD>Apple Computer Commercial Of Venice Wheelchair Ride Wins Addy
Award</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An Apple Computer commercial showing the
wheelchair exploits of a teen-ager on the streets of Venice Beach
claimed top honors at a national advertising awards ceremony.
   The light-hearted Apple commercial, set to Randy Newman's
happy-go-lucky song, ``I'm Different,'' featured 16-year-old actor
Jody Kemp, who lost the use of both legs in an auto accident.
   The advertising spot was named top TV commercial of the year
Sunday at the American Advertising Federation's 20th annual Addy
Awards.
   Produced by the Los Angeles office of BBDO Worldwide, the
commercial offered glimpses of Kemp struggling to get over a curb,
wheeling in to a record shop, and even taking a spill while playing
football. And of course, he was shown at the keys of an Apple
computer.
   The spot was directed by Joe Pytka, whose Venice-based
production company, is best known for doing several of singer
Michael Jackson's Pepsi ads.
