<HEAD>Carper Announces Re-election Plans</HEAD>
<DATELINE>GEORGETOWN, Del. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Delaware's congressman, Democrat Thomas
R. Carper, announced today he plans to seek a fourth term.
   So far, he has no opponent. Carper said he will be disappointed
if he doesn't have a Republican challenger by the July filing
deadline.
   Carper, 41, and his wife, Martha, are expecting their first
child in mid-July. Carper said he wants to spend more time with his
family and will probably cut back slightly in his traditional
grassroots campaign style of trying to meet every resident in the
state.
   Carper told supporters he was concerned about ``the kind of
country and the kind of world in which our child _ our children _
will grow up.''
   ``In a very real way, the actions of our next president and the
next Congress will affect not just the first two or four years of
our children's lives. ... our actions will follow them'' beyond
high school, he said.
   He said the problems facing the nation today include an adequate
defense, health care, decent housing and a competitive economy.
</TEXT>
