<HEAD>Girl Abandoned At Hospital Cafeteria</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DENVER (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A toddler who says her name is Nicki was found
abandoned in a hospital cafeteria with an unsigned note from her
mother, hospital officials said.
   St. Joseph Hospital workers found the girl Sunday morning
sitting alone with a small bag containing clothes, toys and the
note, nursing supervisor Joan Greland said.
   ``The note indicated the mother cares tremendously about her but
there was no way she could handle the situation. She loves her very
much'' but was not able to take care of her, Greland said.
   The child, wearing a white print dress, was ``cheerful and
friendly. She thought everything was just fine,'' Greland said. She
was taken to police headquarters and then to the Denver Social
Services Department shelter, authorities said.
   If the parents are not found, the child will remain in the
shelter while a search goes on for other relatives.
