<HEAD>Boeing 737 Crash Lands, Engine Fire Breaks Out</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW DELHI, India (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A jetliner carrying 123 passengers crash
landed on its belly after its landing gear failed, and an engine
caught fire as the aircraft slid along the runway, an airline
spokesman said today.
   No one was injured in the landing, but the Times of India said
one woman went into shock and had to be sedated.
   The Indian Airlines Boeing 737 made the emergency landing Sunday
night at New Delhi International Airport, according to O.P. Garg, a
spokesman for the airline. He said the plane was on a flight from
the city of Srinagar in the northern state of Kashmir.
   The plane dragged for nearly a mile on the tarmac before air
traffic controllers noticed a fire in its left engine, newspapers
said.
   Firefighters put out the flame with foam, Garg said. At the
time, the passengers and crew were still aboard. They later left
the plane through emergency exits.
   Garg said two pilots had been suspended pending an investigation.
   ``We don't know whether it was human error or mechanical
failure,'' he said.
</TEXT>
