<HEAD>Suspend Classes After Student Demonstrations</HEAD>
<DATELINE>RANGOON, Burma (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Authorities on Monday suspended classes at
a Rangoon university after several days of peaceful student
demonstrations.
   The official government radio said all classes at the Rangoon
Arts and Sciences Univeristy, its affiliate colleges in the capital
and the Institute of Economics were suspended beginning Wednesday.
   The terse announcement did not say why classes were being
suspended nor when they would resume.
