<HEAD>With PM-Summit Rdp Bjt</HEAD>
<HEAD>Reagan Schedules News Conference At Conclusion of Summit</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TORONTO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   President Reagan will hold a news conference
Tuesday after the close of the economic summit of industrialized
nations, his eighth and final meeting with America's chief trading
allies.
   The late-afternoon news conference will follow the reading of
the final summit communique by Canadian Prime Minister Brian
Mulroney, the host of the 14th annual summit of the United States,
Japan, Britain, France, West Germany, Italy and Canada.
   Most, if not all, of the other leaders here also are expected to
hold news conferences Tuesday. The meetings with reporters have
become a tradition of the summit closing in recent years.
   Reagan's last news conference was on June 1 in Moscow following
his summit with Soviet leader Mikhail S. Gorbachev.
 
</TEXT>
