<HEAD>URGENT</HEAD>
<HEAD>Manigat Arrives in Dominican Republic</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SANTO DOMINGO, Dominican Republic (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Haitian President
Leslie Manigat, deposed in a military coup, arrived in the
Dominican Republic today with his family, military sources said.
   Manigat was staying at the Dominican Concorde Hotel, a hotel
spokesman said.
   Lt. Gen. Henri Namphy today declared himself president of Haiti,
which shares the Caribbean island of Hispaniola with the Dominican
Republic.
   The coup ended Manigat's four months as Haiti's civilian
president. The coup came less than a week after Manigat fired
Namphy and tried to reorganize the military.
   Namphy had ruled Haiti as the head of a three-man junta for two
years until Manigat was elected and assumed office Feb. 7
