<2ND_LINE>AM-Abandoned Children,0260</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Woman Abandons Five Children At Hospital, Says She Will Return
Later</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By JAMES LITKE</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>CHICAGO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A woman abandoned five children without
explanation in the emergency room Monday at Cook County Hospital,
saying she would return for them later in the week, a child-welfare
official said.
   ``They're apparently from the same family. They appear to be
healthy, they're well-clothed, well-nourished and there are no
bruises or other indications of abuse,'' said Dave Schneidman,
spokesman for the Illinois Department of Children and Family
Services.
   Schneidman said two of the children are 9-year-old twin boys.
The three remaining children are girls aged 5, 4 and 2.
   ``A woman came into the emergency room this morning and talked
either to a security guard or a bystander. She said, `I'll pick
these children up Thursday,''' said Schneidman, ``and then she just
walked off.''
   The children were taken under protective custody of the agency,
Schneidman said, and after complete physicial examinations, they
could be placed temporarily in foster homes.
   Schneidman said the woman left her name with someone at the
hospital and gave an address at a public-housing project.
   Police are looking for the woman, said Sgt. Steve Scholl.
   ``Everything is slightly `iffy' at this point,'' Schneidman said.
   ``We'd seek permanent custody, or what we call `termination of
parental rights' only as a last step,'' said Schneidman.
   ``We don't want to get ahead of ourselves yet. ... Maybe she
just thought she'd found a unique baby-sitting service.''
</TEXT>
