<HEAD>Former Federated Chairman Dies</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: also contained in PM-Deaths</NOTE>
<DATELINE>CINCINNATI (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Ralph Lazarus, former chairman and chief
executive officer of Federated Department Stores Inc., died after
suffering from a long illness. He was 74.
   Lazarus, who died Sunday, was the grandson of Fred Lazarus,
founder of the F&R Lazarus Co. chain in Columbus. Federated, which
was purchased earlier this year by the Campeau Corp., had been the
parent company of the Lazarus chain.
   Ralph Lazarus, who was raised in Columbus, worked at Lazarus for
more than 22 years and was a graduate of Dartmouth College in
Hanover, N.H.
   His father, Fred Lazarus Jr., co-founded Federated in 1929. It
grew to a nationwide chain of department stores. Ralph Lazarus was
chairman and chief executive officer of Federated from 1972 until
1982. Before that, he was the company's president for 15 years.
</TEXT>
