<1ST_LINE>r f PM-LTV-UnionAgreement     06-20 0229</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-LTV-Union Agreement,0239</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>LTV, Workers Reach Contract Settlement</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DALLAS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   LTV Corp. and the union representing nearly 4,900
aerospace and defense employees have reached a labor contract that
provides modest pay increase and other benefits.
   The new three-year, eight-month labor agreement with the United
Automobile and Aerospace Workers union came on Sunday, two weeks
before the old contract was set to expire on July 2.
   Both sides described the pact as a return to good will between
the union and company.
   ``In this agreement truly both partners won, as did the military
and civilian contractors with whom we do business,'' said Billie
Smith, president of LTV Aircraft Products Group.
   LTV Aircraft Products manufactures aircraft sub-assemblies and
components for military and commercial use and provides extensive
modernization and upgrading of existing military aircraft. It is
one of three divisions of LTV Missiles and Electronics Group, which
also produces electronics, avionics and military vehicles.
   The contract covers 4,894 workers at LTV Aircraft Products and
at the Missiles Division of LTV Missiles and Electronics Group in
Grand Prairie.
   The contract provides general pay increases of 3 percent in the
first and fourth year and one-time performance awards of 3 percent
in the first and fourth years and 5 percent in the second and third
years, the company said.
   The agreement also calls for improvements in employee insurance
and other benefits.
</TEXT>
