<2ND_LINE>PM-USX,0221</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>USX To Sell Transportation Businesses</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PITTSBURGH (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   USX Corp. said today it plans to sell its
transportation businesses for more than $500 million to a joint
venture it is forming with Blackstone Capital Partners.
   USX and Blackstone have signed a letter of intent, leaving a
definitive agreement to be negotiated and regulatory approval,
financing and USX board approval to be obtained, USX said.
   The Blackstone investment group was formed in 1985 by former
Commerce Secretary Peter G. Peterson and Stephen A. Schwarzman,
former head of mergers and acquisitions at Lehman Brothers Kuhn
Loeb Inc., now part of Shearson Lehman Hutton Inc.
   The sale covers all USX's railroads: the Bessemer and Lake Erie;
Birmingham Southern; Duluth, Missabe and Iron Range; Elgin, Joliet
and Eastern; the Lake terminal, and Union Railroad.
   Warrior & Gulf Navigation Co., Pittsburgh & Conneaut Dock Co.,
and USS Great Lakes Fleet Inc. are also included.
   The subsidiaries employ around 4,000 people who operate about
300 locomotives and 20,000 rail cars over more than 2,000 miles of
track, as well as 14 lake vessels, 305 barges and 27 tugboats.
   The Blackstone investors said they will assume labor contracts,
recognize employees' unions and pay comparable benefits to all
employees. They also anticipate no change in customer relations.
</TEXT>
