<1ST_LINE>r f BC-WeeklySteel     06-20 0145</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-Weekly Steel,0146</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Steel Output Fell 5 Percent in Week</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Steel production fell to 1.846 million tons in
the week ended June 18, a decrease of 5.0 percent from the previous
week's 1.944 million tons, the American Iron and Steel Institute
reported Monday.
   The industry's production amounted to 86.1 percent of capacity
during the week, compared with 90.7 percent in the previous week.
   Estimated figures for the year to date showed production at
47.328 million net tons, an increase of 23.2 percent from the
38.420 million net tons in the previous year.
   Production so far this year used 90.8 percent of capacity,
compared with 73.9 percent a year earlier.
   Net tonnage by district for the week ended June 18: Northeast
Coast, 263,000; Pittsburgh, 202,000; Youngstown, 112,000; Lake
Erie, 146,000; Detroit, 150,000; Chicago, 482,000; Midwest,
188,000; Southern, 209,000; and Western, 94,000.
</TEXT>
