<1ST_LINE>r f AM-Forbes-Grave     06-20 0238</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Forbes-Grave,0246</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Publisher Says He Reburied Father In Scotland Because His Heart
Was There</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Flamboyant publisher Malcolm Forbes said Monday he
had his father's body exhumed from a grave in New Jersey and
reburied in his beloved homeland of Scotland.
   ``My father's heart was in Scotland,'' the 69-year-old publisher
said in a television interview on the British Broadcasting Corp.
``Bringing somebody home to a place that they love is a tribute,
not a dig-up or a put-down.''
   Bertie Charles Forbes, who died in 1954 at age 74, was reburied
Sunday in front of St. Kane's Church at New Deer in northeast
Scotland where he worshipped before emigrating to the United States
at the age of 24 to make his fortune in the magazine world.
   Malcolm Forbes said his father was originally buried in
Inglewood, N.J., where he reared his family. But Forbes said he and
his brother decided it was right to take his father's body home and
bury him in the family plot beside his grandfather.
   Over the weekend, Forbes also bought the ruined castle of
Pitsligo, which once belonged to the Forbes clan, for 25,000 pounds
($44,500). He said he wasn't going to restore it but does plan to
conserve it and fix part of it up so that family members can stay
there when they visit Scotland.
   The reburial service for Forbes' father was attended by 13
members of the family.
</TEXT>
