<2ND_LINE>AM-Black & Decker-UK,0159</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Black & Decker Acquires British Toolmaker</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TOWSON, Md. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Black & Decker Corp. has acquired Aven Tools
Ltd., a British maker of high-quality circular saw blades and other
accessories, the company announced Monday.
   Terms of the sale of Aven Tools, which is located in Maltby,
Yorkshire, were not disclosed.
   ``Aven, in the U.K., together with American Emblem Tool Co., a
U.S. accessory manufacturer which we acquired in January 1987, make
Black & Decker one of the leading manufacturers of circular saw
blades in the world,'' said George M. Sherman, president of Black &
Decker's Worldwide Power Tools Group.
   Black & Decker, a maker of power tools and appliances, earlier
this year dropped a bitterly contested, hostile bid to acquire
American Standard Inc., a plumbing and air conditioning
manufacturer.
   American Standard instead was taken private in a $2.5 billion
leveraged buyout led by the investment banker Kelso & Co.
</TEXT>
